<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,764,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[380,428,765,789]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
was collected on a broad-leaf plant alongside the Yamdrok Lake. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Li, Li &amp; Yang, 2013" authorityName="Li, Li &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[268,618,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis box="[268,375,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. longus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li, X. &amp; Li, Z. &amp; Yang, D." box="[384,618,799,824]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="549 - 560" refId="ref24650" refString="Li, X., Li, Z. &amp; Yang, D. (2013) Two new species of Amblypsilopus Bigot with a key to species from Vietnam (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Zootaxa, 3630 (3), 549 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3630.3.9" type="journal article" year="2013">Li, Li &amp; Yang, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[786,885,799,824]" name="Vietnam" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. The Hypopygium of these two species are very similar, but the new species may be separated from the latter by the number of acr and the color of the coxae. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Li &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. longus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are 4 pairs of acr and the mid and hind coxae are wholly yellow (
<bibRefCitation author="Li, X. &amp; Li, Z. &amp; Yang, D." box="[1030,1187,871,896]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="549 - 560" refId="ref24650" refString="Li, X., Li, Z. &amp; Yang, D. (2013) Two new species of Amblypsilopus Bigot with a key to species from Vietnam (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Zootaxa, 3630 (3), 549 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3630.3.9" type="journal article" year="2013">
Li 
<emphasis box="[1063,1112,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
